sql:
SELECT task_name
FROM benchmarking_tasks
WHERE status = 'completed';

SELECT COUNT(*) AS completed_tasks_count
FROM benchmarking_tasks
WHERE status = 'completed';

SELECT relative_diff
FROM benchmarking_results
WHERE result_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- The detailed benchmarking results refer to an extensive set of metrics used to compare the performance of different algorithms and programming languages; 
- Tasks, algorithms, and programming languages are often used interchangeably with projects, models, or problem-solving approaches, software applications or libraries, and coding languages, respectively; 
- Created_at or creation time typically refers to the timestamp when a record was inserted into the database; 
- The results are sorted in descending order, which implies the most recent records will be shown first; 
- Access logs are records of users' interactions with the benchmarking results.

sql:
SELECT task_name
FROM benchmarking_tasks
ORDER BY task_name ASC;

SELECT task_name, description
FROM custom_tasks
WHERE user_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(task_id) AS task_count
FROM custom_tasks
WHERE user_id = 1;

SELECT task_name, status
FROM benchmarking_tasks
WHERE task_id = 1;

SELECT AVG(h2o_time) AS average_h2o_time
FROM benchmarking_results
WHERE algorithm_id = 1;

SELECT task_name, status
FROM benchmarking_tasks
ORDER BY created_at DESC;
